CACHE QUICK GUIDE

Main rule:
- Train only from final cache files (*.pkl that are lists of samples).
- Do not train from checkpoint files (*_checkpoint.pkl). They are only for resuming build_cache.py.

Current cache files:
- cache/cache_hu.pkl
  - Completed HU-only cache.
  - Use for baseline and HU-mask training.
- cache/cache_ts_checkpoint.pkl
  - Partial TotalSegmentator build progress.
  - Use only to resume TS caching.
- cache/cache_ts.pkl
  - Final TS cache. Created only when TS cache build finishes.
  - Use for TS-mask training after it exists.
- cache/cache.pkl / cache/cache_checkpoint.pkl
  - Old/default names. Avoid unless you intentionally rebuild using the default path.

Build HU cache:
- Fresh HU-only build:
  python build_cache.py --no-ts --fresh --cache-path cache/cache_hu.pkl
- Resume HU-only build:
  python build_cache.py --no-ts --cache-path cache/cache_hu.pkl

Build TS cache:
- Fresh TS build:
  python build_cache.py --fresh --cache-path cache/cache_ts.pkl
- Resume TS build after stopping:
  python build_cache.py --cache-path cache/cache_ts.pkl
- Do not add --no-ts for TS.
- Do not add --fresh when resuming, or it restarts from zero.

Stopping safely:
- Prefer Ctrl+C.
- Resume with the same command but without --fresh.
- Do not kill from Task Manager unless necessary, because it can interrupt a checkpoint write.

Status:
- Check progress:
  type cache\cache_status.txt
- TS masks line should increase during TS build.
- If TS masks stays at 0 or many TS WARNING lines appear, TS is failing.

Training commands:
- Baseline on HU cache:
  python baseline.py --cache-path cache/cache_hu.pkl
- HU-mask training:
  python train.py --mask-type hu --cache-path cache/cache_hu.pkl
- TS-mask training after cache/cache_ts.pkl exists:
  python train.py --mask-type ts --cache-path cache/cache_ts.pkl

Fair HU vs TS comparison:
- Best/fair comparison is both masks from the same completed TS cache:
  python train.py --mask-type hu --cache-path cache/cache_ts.pkl
  python train.py --mask-type ts --cache-path cache/cache_ts.pkl
- This keeps the patient/sample set matched.
- If using cache_hu.pkl for HU and cache_ts.pkl for TS, results may use different cohorts.

Important logic:
- HU cache stores:
  image, HU mask, label, patient_id, ts_mask=None
- TS cache stores:
  image, HU mask, TS mask, label, patient_id
- load_nodules_hu uses the HU mask field.
- load_nodules_ts uses the TS mask field and drops samples where ts_mask is None.
- patient_split splits by patient_id, so train/val/test should not share patients.

When to use --fresh:
- Use --fresh when starting a new cache from zero.
- Use --fresh after changing build_cache.py mask logic or config values that affect cache content.
- Do not use --fresh to resume an interrupted cache.

Small smoke test:
- Quick HU-only test:
  python build_cache.py --no-ts --fresh --sample-size 50 --cache-path cache/cache_test_hu.pkl
- Quick TS test:
  python build_cache.py --fresh --sample-size 5 --cache-path cache/cache_test_ts.pkl

Cleanup notes:
- Safe to delete old/default cache_checkpoint.pkl if not using cache/cache.pkl anymore.
- Keep cache_ts_checkpoint.pkl until TS cache finishes.
- Keep cache_hu.pkl because it is the completed HU data.
